25|$|One AIR-4 was {{modified}} as the Yakovlev AIR-4MK in 1933 to test nearly full-span split flaps. Floating wingtips, which provided <b>roll</b> <b>control,</b> {{were added to}} release as much trailing edge as possible for the flaps.|$|E
40|$|Magnus {{forces and}} moments were {{measured}} on a basic-finner model spinning in transonic flow. Spin was induced by canted fins or by full-span or semi-span, outboard and inboard <b>roll</b> <b>controls.</b> Magnus force and moment reversals were caused by Mach number, reduced spin rate, and angle of attack variations. Magnus center of pressure {{was found to be}} independent of the angle of attack but varied with the Mach number and model configuration or reduced spin rate...|$|R
